description:
TPO 121/14 - T57 (London Plane) - crown lift to provide 3m clearance from ground level;
T58 (Sycamore) - cut back from building by 2m;
T60 (Silver Birch) - cut back from lamp column by 1m;
G4 (Robinia x 4) - remove major deadwood throughout whole crown area;
T6 (Oak) - remove major deadwood throughout whole crown area;
T4 and T34 (Ash) - Sever ivy;
T3 - (Horse Chestnut) - fell above close to ground level by sectional lopping and roping down as necessary;
T43 (Ash, Thorn, Ivy) - cut back to edge of parking bay;
T44 (Holly) - cut back to edge of kerb line;
T46 (Beech) - sever and remove ivy;
T333 (Ash stems) - fell right hand stem with centre cavity close to ground level by sectional lopping and roping down as necessary;
T38a (Common Horse chestnut) - remove major deadwood throughout whole crown area; and
G5 (Ash, Sycamore, Robinia, Holly) - remove major deadwood throughout whole crown area. (Summary).
